does anyone recall the rules discussed around pattern window growth throughout the day? 

i remember there being a rule about it’s minimum state staying fixed until mid-morning (idk, around 9am?) and only expanding after that so early morning users could see a reasonable view of their pattern.
on the other end of that, should the window expand to the very top of the bottom nav bar at EOD or stop with enough room to show a peek of the first Dx card still?
Good question Trent. <@U0260V1BX> do you know the answer there? Also wondering if that's outlined in our wires because it will be helpful/needed definition for dev

I don’t know how much of the specifics we’ve figured out. Not being able to test it has probably left us leaving this a bit open. The idea is explained in Melissa’s wires for Homescreen. 6.1 page 5
>When opening the app, the pattern area height should correspond to the current time of day, and the user should see the last metrics and density of the pattern as well as the last icon set / minute count.
>Visual design will determine a minimum height and zero-state pattern to be displayed in the morning. See Spec.

initial thoughts were to keep some room for a peek of the first Dx card. I also know that we’re playing with the idea of what actually lives below the pattern in certain situations.

For me, I think it could help for it to grow all the way down to the tab bar, so that it better connects with the previous day views.
The user tests told me, at least, that we may be able to de-emphasize the role of Dx card on home beyond a short-cut to stuff i’m enrolled in
it might be worth taking a look at what we’re really missing if we grow it all the way down to the tab bar
It might also be worthwhile talking to dev about it what determines the hight, especially when we need to consider different phone sizes.
